🧠 1. What is UptimeRobot (in simple but real terms)

Think of UptimeRobot as:

A robot sitting somewhere on the internet that keeps checking:
“Is your website alive or dead?”

🔁 What it does internally

Every X minutes (like 1 min, 5 min):

UptimeRobot → sends HTTP request → your website

Example:

GET https://yourapi.com/health
🟢 If response is OK (200)

→ Status = UP

🔴 If no response / error

→ Status = DOWN

🚨 Then comes the important part

When status changes:

UP → DOWN  OR  DOWN → UP

It triggers a notification

That notification can be:

Email
SMS
Slack
Webhook (this is what YOU use)
🔗 2. What that paragraph actually means

Let’s decode it properly:

“Client signs up → gets webhook URL → pastes into UptimeRobot → done”

💡 Real flow (step-by-step)
Step 1: User signs up on YOUR platform

You create a team:

{
  "teamId": "team_123"
}
Step 2: You give them a webhook URL

Something like:

https://yourapp.com/api/webhooks/uptime/team_123

👉 This is YOUR backend endpoint

Step 3: User goes to UptimeRobot dashboard

They:
Add a monitor (their website)
Go to Alert Contacts
Choose Webhook
Paste your URL
Step 4: Now UptimeRobot does everything

You don’t touch their server.

UptimeRobot:
pings their site every 5 mins
detects downtime
sends POST request to your backend
Step 5: When site goes DOWN

UptimeRobot sends:
POST /api/webhooks/uptime/team_123

Body (example):
{
  "alertType": "DOWN",
  "monitorName": "API Server",
  "url": "https://api.client.com"
}

Step 6: Your backend reacts
→ create incident
→ insert event (monitor_down)
→ notify team
Step 7: When site comes back UP

Another webhook:
{
  "alertType": "UP"
}

Then:
→ update incident
→ insert event (monitor_up)
→ prompt resolve
⚙️ 3. Backend Code (IMPORTANT)

Assume you're using Node.js + Express
app.post("/api/webhooks/uptime/:teamId", async (req, res) => {
  const { teamId } = req.params;
  const payload = req.body;

  const isDown = payload.alertType === "DOWN";
  const isUp = payload.alertType === "UP";

  if (isDown) {
    // 1. Create incident
    const incident = await createIncident({
      teamId,
      title: `${payload.monitorName} is DOWN`,
      status: "investigating"
    });

    // 2. Insert event
    await createEvent({
      incidentId: incident.id,
      type: "monitor_down",
      message: `${payload.monitorName} is DOWN`
    });

  } else if (isUp) {
    // Find latest open incident
    const incident = await findActiveIncident(teamId);

    // Add event
    await createEvent({
      incidentId: incident.id,
      type: "monitor_up",
      message: `${payload.monitorName} is UP`
    });

    // Update status
    await updateIncidentStatus(incident.id, "monitoring");
  }

  res.sendStatus(200);
});


4. How to Generate Webhook URL (VERY IMPORTANT)

You don’t hardcode URLs.

Each team gets a unique endpoint

(Better - secure)
Add a secret token:
const webhookUrl = `https://yourapp.com/api/webhooks/uptime/${team.id}?token=abc123`;

